President Donald J. Trump met with European Council President Donald Tusk and European Commission President Jean-Claude Juncker in Brussels. They reaffirmed the strong bond between the United States and Europe and discussed shared challenges in fighting global terrorism and protecting homelands. They agreed to deepen security cooperation in fighting ISIS, combating radicalization, and responding to common threats. They also discussed the threat from North Korea and agreed to work together to isolate the regime politically and economically. The leaders emphasized the need to deepen the strong economic relationship between the United States and the European Union and to protect industries against unfair competition.